"In 1773 he published antislavery articles in the Connecticut Journal under the pseudonym 'Antidoulios' — Greek for 'against slavery.' His 1791 sermon 'The Injustice and Impolicy of the Slave Trade' delivered antislavery from his New Haven pulpit."},{"number":2,"category":"legacy","header":"Mohican linguist — Washington thanked him personally","body":"He grew up in Stockbridge speaking Mohican before English, writing that 'it became more familiar to me than my mother tongue.' His 1788 'Observations on the Language of the Muhhekaneew Indians' was acknowledged by George Washington and circulated through Madison to Jefferson."},{"number":3,"category":"family","header":"His first wife drowned at New Haven 1782","body":"His first wife Mary Porter died June 10, 1782 in New Haven by drowning, leaving four children. He remarried in December 1783 to Mary Sabins, with whom he had no further children."},{"number":4,"category":"death","header":"Died as president of Union College, 1801","body":"In May 1799 he was chosen President of Union College in Schenectady, New York. He served less than two years, dying in office August 1, 1801, age 56 — leaving the abolitionist Edwards line for his sons to carry."},{"number":5,"category":"social_reform","header":"He wrote against slavery as “Antidoulios”","body":"Ordained only four years, the twenty-eight-year-old pastor took a pen name for his 1773 newspaper attack on slavery: Antidoulios, Greek for “against slavery.” He applied the golden rule directly — why are slaveholders exempt from “whatsoever ye would that men should do to you”?"}],"education":[{"school_name":"Princeton (College of New Jersey)","dates":"1765","type":"undergraduate","notes":"ranked first in a class of thirty-one"},{"school_name":"Theology under Joseph Bellamy","location":"Bethlehem, Connecticut","type":"professional"}],"career":[{"role":"Tutor","organization":"Princeton","start_year":1767,"end_year":1769},{"role":"Pastor","organization":"White Haven (2nd Congregational) Church, New Haven","start_year":1769,"end_year":1795},{"role":"Pastor","organization":"Colebrook, Connecticut","start_year":1795,"end_year":1799},{"role":"President","organization":"Union College, Schenectady","start_year":1799,"end_year":1801}],"slug":"jonathan-edwards-1745"}},"burialCemetery":null,"institutionsById":{},"crossConnections":[]}